1
00:01:31,500 --> 00:01:34,418
Help! Someone help me!

2
00:01:37,630 --> 00:01:39,756
Is someone there?

3
00:01:40,841 --> 00:01:42,884
Hey!

4
00:01:45,220 --> 00:01:47,221
Oh, shit, I'm probably dead.

5
00:01:47,305 --> 00:01:50,015
You're not dead.
-Who's that?

6
00:01:50,100 --> 00:01:52,101
Who's that?

7
00:01:52,185 --> 00:01:54,895
There's no point in yelling,
I already tried that.

8
00:01:54,979 --> 00:01:57,231
Turn on the lights!

9
00:01:57,315 --> 00:01:59,525
I would if I could.

10
00:01:59,608 --> 00:02:02,902
What the fuck is going on?
Where am I?

11
00:02:02,986 --> 00:02:06,531
-I don't know yet.
-What is that smell?

12
00:02:06,615 --> 00:02:10,785
Shh. Hang on a second.
I think I found something.

13
00:02:57,704 --> 00:02:59,079
Holy shit.

14
00:03:14,720 --> 00:03:16,762
Aaaargh! Help!

15
00:03:19,056 --> 00:03:20,599
Help!

16
00:03:22,518 --> 00:03:24,144
Help!

17
00:03:25,396 --> 00:03:26,813
Help!

18
00:03:27,607 --> 00:03:29,941
No-one can hear you.

19
00:03:30,025 --> 00:03:32,234
What the fuck is this?

20
00:03:32,319 --> 00:03:35,988
Calm down. Just calm down.

21
00:03:36,072 --> 00:03:37,281
Are you hurt?

22
00:03:38,700 --> 00:03:40,701
I don't know. Yeah!

23
00:03:40,784 --> 00:03:44,412
-What's your name?
-My name is Very Fucking Confused.

24
00:03:44,496 --> 00:03:47,123
What's your name?
What's going on here?

25
00:03:47,208 --> 00:03:51,169
My name is Lawrence Gordon, I'm a doctor.
I just woke up here, like you.

26
00:04:00,470 --> 00:04:02,346
Aaaargh!

27
00:04:03,723 --> 00:04:05,974
Recognize him?

28
00:04:06,059 --> 00:04:07,684
No.

29
00:04:10,562 --> 00:04:12,605
Do you have any idea how you got here?

30
00:04:12,689 --> 00:04:14,440
No.

31
00:04:14,524 --> 00:04:17,401
-What's the last thing you remember?
-Nothing.

32
00:04:17,486 --> 00:04:21,864
I went to bed in my shit-hole apartment,
and woke up in an actual shit-hole.

33
00:04:24,867 --> 00:04:27,285
What about you, huh?

34
00:04:27,370 --> 00:04:30,872
There's... There's not much to tell.

35
00:04:32,540 --> 00:04:35,376
I was on my way home from work, and...

36
00:04:35,460 --> 00:04:37,503
I don't remember anything else.

37
00:04:42,342 --> 00:04:44,343
First dead body I've ever seen.

38
00:04:45,469 --> 00:04:47,178
They look different in real life.

39
00:04:49,306 --> 00:04:51,349
They don't move.

40
00:04:56,063 --> 00:04:58,982
From the looks of these chains,

41
00:04:59,065 --> 00:05:01,817
someone didn't want us
to go very far, either.

42
00:05:02,735 --> 00:05:06,196
-Can you see any scars?
-What?

43
00:05:06,280 --> 00:05:08,073
Man, they kidnap you and drug you.

44
00:05:08,157 --> 00:05:11,076
Before you know, you're in a bath
and your kidneys are on eBay.

45
00:05:11,159 --> 00:05:13,786
No-one has taken your kidneys.

46
00:05:13,870 --> 00:05:16,580
How can you tell from way over there?

47
00:05:16,665 --> 00:05:20,000
You'd either be in terrible agony,
or you'd be dead by now.

48
00:05:20,085 --> 00:05:21,460
Trust me.

49
00:05:21,545 --> 00:05:23,587
-What are you, a surgeon?
-Yeah.

50
00:05:27,007 --> 00:05:28,007
So...

51
00:05:29,552 --> 00:05:32,137
Are you gonna tell me
your name, or what?

52
00:05:35,599 --> 00:05:37,642
Adam.

53
00:05:38,810 --> 00:05:40,853
Well, Adam...

54
00:05:42,188 --> 00:05:44,732
What we need to do...

55
00:05:44,816 --> 00:05:47,151
is start thinking about why we're here.

56
00:05:47,235 --> 00:05:50,779
Whoever brought us here
could have killed us by now.

57
00:05:50,863 --> 00:05:52,155
But they didn't.

58
00:05:53,073 --> 00:05:55,116
They must want something from us.

59
00:05:57,035 --> 00:05:59,078
The question is, what?

60
00:06:03,833 --> 00:06:06,918
-That clock.
-What about it?

61
00:06:07,003 --> 00:06:09,963
-It's brand-new.
-So?

62
00:06:10,047 --> 00:06:13,967
So... somebody obviously
wanted us to know the time.

63
00:06:17,596 --> 00:06:20,806
Wait, I think I might be
able to reach the door.

64
00:06:45,580 --> 00:06:47,706
What is that?

65
00:06:51,211 --> 00:06:52,502
Excuse me.

66
00:06:52,587 --> 00:06:54,546
It's a tape.

67
00:06:54,630 --> 00:06:57,548
-Where did you find it?
-It was in my pocket.

68
00:07:05,849 --> 00:07:07,892
It says, "Play me. "

69
00:07:39,380 --> 00:07:41,422
Come on. Come on.

70
00:07:44,301 --> 00:07:46,052
Throw it over here.

71
00:07:53,434 --> 00:07:55,185
Fuck.

72
00:08:06,571 --> 00:08:07,863
No?

73
00:08:33,805 --> 00:08:37,391
-Use your shirt.
-What?

74
00:08:37,475 --> 00:08:39,518
Your shirt.

75
00:08:53,364 --> 00:08:55,365
Come on.

76
00:09:00,496 --> 00:09:02,497
-It won't work.
-Look around.

77
00:09:02,582 --> 00:09:04,624
There must be something else you can use.

78
00:09:04,708 --> 00:09:08,461
-There's nothing.
-Well, there must be something.

79
00:09:21,474 --> 00:09:23,516
Come on. You can do it.

80
00:09:28,230 --> 00:09:29,522
Come on. Come on.

81
00:09:29,606 --> 00:09:30,898
Again.

82
00:09:53,670 --> 00:09:55,963
Rise and shine, Adam.

83
00:09:56,047 --> 00:09:58,507
You're probably wondering where you are.

84
00:09:58,591 --> 00:10:01,092
I'll tell you where you might be.

85
00:10:01,177 --> 00:10:04,054
You might be in the room that you die in.

86
00:10:04,138 --> 00:10:10,060
Up until now, you've simply sat in the shadows,
watching others live out their lives.

87
00:10:10,143 --> 00:10:14,438
But what do voyeurs see
when they look into the mirror?

88
00:10:14,522 --> 00:10:20,152
Now, I see you as a strange mix
of someone angry yet apathetic.

89
00:10:20,237 --> 00:10:22,238
But mostly just pathetic.

90
00:10:22,321 --> 00:10:25,490
So, are you going to watch
yourself die today, Adam,

91
00:10:25,574 --> 00:10:27,617
or do something about it?

92
00:10:29,078 --> 00:10:31,120
I don't get it.

93
00:10:31,997 --> 00:10:33,248
Throw me the player.

94
00:10:35,583 --> 00:10:38,460
No. You throw me your tape.

95
00:10:39,796 --> 00:10:43,590
Look, we're gonna have to work together,
if we want to get out of here.

96
00:10:43,675 --> 00:10:46,134
-Throw it to me.
-I'm not gonna risk breaking it.

97
00:10:46,219 --> 00:10:48,262
You throw me your tape.

98
00:11:05,152 --> 00:11:07,153
Dr. Gordon...

99
00:11:07,238 --> 00:11:09,739
this is your wake-up call.

100
00:11:09,824 --> 00:11:13,660
Every day of your working life,
you have given people the news

101
00:11:13,743 --> 00:11:16,120
that they're gonna die soon.

102
00:11:16,204 --> 00:11:20,040
Now you will be the cause of death.

103
00:11:20,125 --> 00:11:24,044
Your aim in this game is to kill Adam.

104
00:11:24,129 --> 00:11:26,213
You have until 6 on the clock to do it.

105
00:11:27,506 --> 00:11:30,091
There's a man in the room with you.

106
00:11:30,175 --> 00:11:32,760
When there's that much poison in your blood,

107
00:11:32,845 --> 00:11:36,431
the only thing left to do is shoot yourself.

108
00:11:42,478 --> 00:11:46,857
There are ways to win this,
hidden all around you.

109
00:11:46,941 --> 00:11:52,279
Just remember,
X marks the spot for the treasure.

110
00:11:52,362 --> 00:11:55,239
If you do not kill Adam by six,

111
00:11:56,616 --> 00:12:00,119
then Alison and Diana will die,
Dr. Gordon.

112
00:12:01,204 --> 00:12:04,540
And I'll leave you in
this room to rot.

113
00:12:05,833 --> 00:12:07,876
Let the game begin.

114
00:12:17,343 --> 00:12:19,344
Give me that.

115
00:12:19,429 --> 00:12:20,554
Now.

116
00:12:29,564 --> 00:12:32,983
Then Alison and Diana will die,
Dr. Gordon...

117
00:12:34,109 --> 00:12:36,944
...and I'll leave you in
this room to rot.

118
00:12:37,029 --> 00:12:42,200
-Any idea who that is?
-Let the game begin.

119
00:12:42,284 --> 00:12:45,953
-He knows us.
-Wait a minute.

120
00:12:46,037 --> 00:12:49,122
What do you think? Probably a joke, right?

121
00:12:49,207 --> 00:12:50,707
Shh!

122
00:12:50,791 --> 00:12:54,044
-Let the game begin.
-Listen. Listen.

123
00:12:55,129 --> 00:12:57,130
Follow your heart.

124
00:13:04,888 --> 00:13:07,139
What the hell does "follow your heart" mean?

125
00:13:13,729 --> 00:13:16,940
There, right next to you, on the toilet.

126
00:13:26,533 --> 00:13:29,535
Come on. Come on.

127
00:13:33,206 --> 00:13:35,249
Oh, man!

128
00:13:43,131 --> 00:13:45,883
-Anything?
-No solids.

129
00:13:45,968 --> 00:13:47,301
Take off the lid.

130
00:13:49,845 --> 00:13:51,471
Come on.

131
00:14:01,356 --> 00:14:03,607
I really wish I had've checked in there first.

132
00:14:03,692 --> 00:14:05,859
Huh! What is it?

133
00:14:34,762 --> 00:14:36,013
Hey.

134
00:14:37,640 --> 00:14:39,099
Mind passing me the other one?

135
00:15:06,166 --> 00:15:08,208
Fuck! Fuck!

136
00:15:51,666 --> 00:15:54,251
He doesn't want us to cut through our chains.

137
00:15:56,087 --> 00:15:58,130
He wants us to cut through our feet.

138
00:16:02,134 --> 00:16:04,344
I think I may know who's done this to us.

139
00:16:04,428 --> 00:16:06,846
What did you say?

140
00:16:06,931 --> 00:16:08,973
Well, it's not someone I know personally.

141
00:16:09,891 --> 00:16:11,517
It's just someone I know of.

142
00:16:12,602 --> 00:16:15,062
Jesus Christ! Tell me. Who is it?

143
00:16:17,524 --> 00:16:19,566
Last I heard...

144
00:16:20,777 --> 00:16:23,445
.. the police still hadn't caught him.

145
00:16:23,529 --> 00:16:25,863
And the only reason I know that...

146
00:16:25,948 --> 00:16:27,990
is because I was a suspect.

147
00:16:30,410 --> 00:16:32,453
I'll start from the beginning.

148
00:16:39,669 --> 00:16:43,713
This one's not fresh any more.
At least three weeks out.

149
00:16:43,798 --> 00:16:47,050
Victim's a 46-year-old male.

150
00:16:48,593 --> 00:16:53,264
Died of massive blood loss,
mostly through the femoral artery.

151
00:16:56,810 --> 00:17:00,396
He started at the back and tunneled
through that razor wire so fast,

152
00:17:00,480 --> 00:17:02,523
it's amazing he got as far as he did.

153
00:17:04,692 --> 00:17:08,736
Cut himself so deep,
we found traces of stomach acid on the floor.

154
00:17:13,575 --> 00:17:15,285
We also found this.

155
00:17:18,705 --> 00:17:24,084
Hello, Paul. You are a
perfectly healthy, sane, middle-class male,

156
00:17:24,168 --> 00:17:25,502
yet last month,

157
00:17:25,586 --> 00:17:28,255
you ran a straight razor across your wrists.

158
00:17:30,048 --> 00:17:33,134
Did you cut yourself
because you truly wanted to die,

159
00:17:33,218 --> 00:17:35,845
or did you just want some attention?

160
00:17:35,929 --> 00:17:38,472
Tonight, you'll show me.

161
00:17:38,557 --> 00:17:41,517
The irony is that if you want to die,

162
00:17:41,600 --> 00:17:44,019
you just have to stay where you are.

163
00:17:44,103 --> 00:17:46,688
If you want to live,
you'll have to cut yourself again.

164
00:17:46,772 --> 00:17:49,941
Find a path through the razor wire to the door.

165
00:17:50,026 --> 00:17:51,359
But hurry.

166
00:17:52,528 --> 00:17:55,447
At three o'clock that door will lock.

167
00:17:55,530 --> 00:17:58,032
And then this room becomes your tomb.

168
00:17:58,116 --> 00:18:01,452
How much blood will you shed
to stay alive, Paul?

169
00:18:05,040 --> 00:18:08,459
Door was on a timer.
It was unlocked until three o'clock.

170
00:18:09,877 --> 00:18:13,337
Then it slammed shut. He was given two hours.

171
00:18:15,799 --> 00:18:17,925
You sick fuck!

172
00:18:23,723 --> 00:18:25,432
A jigsaw piece.

173
00:18:30,313 --> 00:18:33,148
I think we're gonna be here for a while, Sing.

174
00:18:33,231 --> 00:18:36,942
The newspapers started
calling him "the jigsaw killer".

175
00:18:37,027 --> 00:18:40,362
Actually, technically speaking,

176
00:18:40,447 --> 00:18:43,991
he's... not really a murderer.

177
00:18:45,659 --> 00:18:47,577
He never killed anyone.

178
00:18:47,661 --> 00:18:50,705
He finds ways for his victims
to kill themselves.

179
00:18:53,417 --> 00:18:56,586
Hello, Mark. If you're so sick,

180
00:18:56,670 --> 00:18:59,881
then why do I have so many photos of you
up and about?

181
00:19:00,548 --> 00:19:03,842
Let's put your so-called illness to the test.

182
00:19:05,178 --> 00:19:09,056
Right now, there's a slow-acting
poison in your veins.

183
00:19:09,140 --> 00:19:12,142
The antidote is inside the safe.

184
00:19:12,226 --> 00:19:13,267
Help!

185
00:19:14,353 --> 00:19:18,481
The combination to the safe...
is written on the wall.

186
00:19:18,565 --> 00:19:20,650
Hurry up and program it in.

187
00:19:20,734 --> 00:19:22,860
But watch your step.

188
00:19:22,945 --> 00:19:28,199
By the way, that's a flammable substance
smeared on your body.

189
00:19:28,282 --> 00:19:31,493
So, I would be careful
with that candle, if I were you.

190
00:19:31,577 --> 00:19:37,332
Or all the people you've burned with your act
just might have their revenge.

191
00:19:41,836 --> 00:19:43,045
Aaaargh!

192
00:19:44,381 --> 00:19:45,756
I found something else.

193
00:19:46,883 --> 00:19:48,884
Well, two things, actually.

194
00:19:48,969 --> 00:19:52,221
There was someone standing outside,
watching through this hole.

195
00:19:52,304 --> 00:19:57,141
Our friend Jigsaw likes to book himself
front-row seats to his own sick little games.

196
00:19:57,226 --> 00:19:59,519
He was there at the last one as well.

197
00:20:00,646 --> 00:20:03,982
Only, this time... he left us his penlight.

198
00:20:07,902 --> 00:20:09,444
Hm...

199
00:20:10,530 --> 00:20:12,531
Get a rush on the prints.

200
00:20:12,615 --> 00:20:14,992
Copy that.

201
00:20:15,076 --> 00:20:19,079
This patient has an inoperable frontal lobe
tumor extending across the midline.

202
00:20:19,162 --> 00:20:21,998
It started as colon cancer.

203
00:20:22,082 --> 00:20:25,334
The patient has come in for a standard checkup,

204
00:20:25,419 --> 00:20:29,046
by which we can monitor the rate
at which his condition is declining.

205
00:20:29,130 --> 00:20:31,548
-The patient had...
-His name is John.

206
00:20:32,758 --> 00:20:35,927
Dr. Gordon. He's a very interesting person.

207
00:20:38,639 --> 00:20:40,640
Thank you for that information, Zep.

208
00:20:40,725 --> 00:20:44,686
As you can see, our orderlies
form very special bonds with the patients.

209
00:20:46,021 --> 00:20:48,063
Continuing on, the patient had...

210
00:20:48,148 --> 00:20:50,983
Dr. Gordon, please page the operator.

211
00:20:52,527 --> 00:20:57,031
Someone doesn't want me to tell you
what the patient had! Excuse me.

212
00:21:01,785 --> 00:21:03,077
Dr. Gordon.

213
00:21:04,204 --> 00:21:07,415
I'm Detective Tapp, this is Detective Sing.
City homicide.

214
00:21:07,498 --> 00:21:12,210
-Very impressive.
-Oh, thank you.

215
00:21:12,295 --> 00:21:14,046
I do my best.

216
00:21:16,799 --> 00:21:19,176
-Sorry to interrupt you while you work.
-Fine.

217
00:21:19,260 --> 00:21:21,303
Now, how can I help you gentlemen?

218
00:21:21,386 --> 00:21:27,266
Are you able to tell us where you were
between the hours of 11 PM and 1 AM last night?

219
00:21:27,350 --> 00:21:30,227
Why is it that you're interested?

220
00:21:30,312 --> 00:21:32,730
We'd like to ask a few questions about it.

221
00:21:32,813 --> 00:21:37,484
For your sake, I think it's best
if we do it down at the station.

222
00:21:37,568 --> 00:21:42,197
-Would you like to follow us there?
-I'm afraid that's out of the question.

223
00:21:42,281 --> 00:21:46,576
I can't just leave, I have work to do.
Plus my wife has the car today.

224
00:21:46,659 --> 00:21:48,994
That's OK. You can ride with us.

225
00:21:49,079 --> 00:21:50,412
Doc?

226
00:21:54,417 --> 00:21:57,044
I'm sorry.

227
00:21:57,128 --> 00:22:00,798
You'll have to tell me again.
What is this all about?

228
00:22:01,924 --> 00:22:03,966
Is this yours, Doctor?

229
00:22:16,604 --> 00:22:20,148
So you have no idea how your penlight
showed up at the murder scene?

230
00:22:20,233 --> 00:22:22,275
Of course not, Brett.

231
00:22:25,695 --> 00:22:28,948
Well, I have to ask.
What were you doing last night?

232
00:22:31,868 --> 00:22:33,911
I was seeing someone.

233
00:22:35,539 --> 00:22:36,914
Who?

234
00:22:40,584 --> 00:22:42,961
Look, if you can't be honest with me...

235
00:22:43,045 --> 00:22:45,088
I was visiting someone, It wasn't a patient.

236
00:22:45,172 --> 00:22:47,048
All right?

237
00:22:49,468 --> 00:22:51,469
What am I gonna do?

238
00:22:51,553 --> 00:22:54,137
Well, as your lawyer and your friend,

239
00:22:54,222 --> 00:22:59,518
my advice to you is to bite the bullet
and give them your alibi now,

240
00:22:59,602 --> 00:23:01,770
cos no-one's gonna believe you later.

241
00:23:07,317 --> 00:23:09,360
That was five months ago.

242
00:23:12,990 --> 00:23:15,032
He tried to set me up for murder.

243
00:23:18,911 --> 00:23:20,537
OK.

244
00:23:21,622 --> 00:23:23,999
We checked your alibi, It holds up.

245
00:23:24,083 --> 00:23:27,252
Good. Can I go home now?

246
00:23:27,336 --> 00:23:30,630
We have one of the victims
who managed to escape.

247
00:23:30,714 --> 00:23:35,092
Want to know if you wouldn't mind sticking
around and listening to her testimony.

248
00:23:35,176 --> 00:23:37,177
Maybe it'll trigger something.

249
00:23:37,262 --> 00:23:41,348
-I'd like to help, really, but...
-Well, we'd appreciate it.

250
00:23:41,433 --> 00:23:43,934
-She's the only one who made it.
-OK.

251
00:23:49,940 --> 00:23:51,566
Amanda...

252
00:23:52,651 --> 00:23:55,069
In your own time...

253
00:23:55,153 --> 00:23:57,821
tell me the first thing you remember.

254
00:24:12,085 --> 00:24:14,211
I woke up.

255
00:24:14,296 --> 00:24:16,464
All I could taste was blood.

256
00:24:18,175 --> 00:24:19,717
And metal.

257
00:24:48,911 --> 00:24:50,953
Hello, Amanda.

